The President's Weekly Address discusses the significance of the Battle of Yorktown, which marked America's victory in gaining independence from Britain. The address highlights the symbolism of the American flag and emphasizes the importance of respecting and honoring it. It also mentions the sacrifices made by men and women in uniform to protect the flag. The address concludes by urging citizens to love their country, protect fellow citizens, and maintain America as the land of the free and the home of the brave.